  version: New Living Translation
  ver: NLT
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from James
      content: "This letter is from James, a slave of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ.\n\tI
        am writing to the \u201Ctwelve tribes\u201D\u2014Jewish believers scattered
        abroad.\n\tGreetings!  "
      comments: []
    - title: Faith and Endurance
      content: 'Dear brothers and sisters,[COMMENT[0]] when troubles of any kind
        come your way, consider it an opportunity for great joy. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'brothers; '
        - ft: also in 1:16, 19.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'For you know that when your faith is tested, your endurance has a
        chance to grow. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So let it grow, for when your endurance is fully developed, you will
        be perfect and complete, needing nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you need wisdom, ask our generous God, and he will give it to
        you. He will not rebuke you for asking. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when you ask him, be sure that your faith is in God alone. Do
        not waver, for a person with divided loyalty is as unsettled as a wave of
        the sea that is blown and tossed by the wind. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Such people should not expect to receive anything from the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their loyalty is divided between God and the world, and they are
        unstable in everything they do.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Believers who are[COMMENT[0]] poor have something to boast about,
        for God has honored them. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: The brother who is.
    - title: 
      content: 'And those who are rich should boast that God has humbled them. They
        will fade away like a little flower in the field. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The hot sun rises and the grass withers; the little flower droops
        and falls, and its beauty fades away. In the same way, the rich will fade
        away with all of their achievements.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God blesses those who patiently endure testing and temptation. Afterward
        they will receive the crown of life that God has promised to those who love
        him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And remember, when you are being tempted, do not say, \u201CGod is
        tempting me.\u201D God is never tempted to do wrong,[COMMENT[0]] and he never
        tempts anyone else. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: God should not be put to a test by evil people.
    - title: 
      content: 'Temptation comes from our own desires, which entice us and drag us
        away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These desires give birth to sinful actions. And when sin is allowed
        to grow, it gives birth to death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So don\u2019t be misled, my dear brothers and sisters. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whatever is good and perfect is a gift coming down to us from God
        our Father, who created all the lights in the heavens.[COMMENT[0]] He never
        changes or casts a shifting shadow.[COMMENT[1]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:17a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: from above, from the Father of lights.
      - number: '1:17b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: He never changes, as a shifting shadow does.
    - title: 
      content: 'He chose to give birth to us by giving us his true word. And we,
        out of all creation, became his prized possession.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: we became a kind of firstfruit of his creatures.
    - title: Listening and Doing
      content: 'Understand this, my dear brothers and sisters: You must all be quick
        to listen, slow to speak, and slow to get angry. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Human anger[COMMENT[0]] does not produce the righteousness[COMMENT[1]]
        God desires. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:20a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: "A man\u2019s anger."
      - number: '1:20b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: the justice.
    - title: 
      content: 'So get rid of all the filth and evil in your lives, and humbly accept
        the word God has planted in your hearts, for it has the power to save your
        souls.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But don\u2019t just listen to God\u2019s word. You must do what it
        says. Otherwise, you are only fooling yourselves. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For if you listen to the word and don\u2019t obey, it is like glancing
        at your face in a mirror. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You see yourself, walk away, and forget what you look like. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you look carefully into the perfect law that sets you free,
        and if you do what it says and don\u2019t forget what you heard, then God
        will bless you for doing it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you claim to be religious but don\u2019t control your tongue,
        you are fooling yourself, and your religion is worthless. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Pure and genuine religion in the sight of God the Father means caring
        for orphans and widows in their distress and refusing to let the world corrupt
        you.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Warning against Prejudice
      content: 'My dear brothers and sisters,[COMMENT[0]] how can you claim to have
        faith in our glorious Lord Jesus Christ if you favor some people over others?  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'brothers; '
        - ft: also in 2:5, 14.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'For example, suppose someone comes into your meeting[COMMENT[0]]
        dressed in fancy clothes and expensive jewelry, and another comes in who
        is poor and dressed in dirty clothes. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: your synagogue.
    - title: 
      content: "If you give special attention and a good seat to the rich person,
        but you say to the poor one, \u201CYou can stand over there, or else sit
        on the floor\u201D\u2014well, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "doesn\u2019t this discrimination show that your judgments are guided
        by evil motives?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to me, dear brothers and sisters. Hasn\u2019t God chosen the
        poor in this world to be rich in faith? Aren\u2019t they the ones who will
        inherit the Kingdom he promised to those who love him? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you dishonor the poor! Isn\u2019t it the rich who oppress you
        and drag you into court? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Aren\u2019t they the ones who slander Jesus Christ, whose noble name[COMMENT[0]]
        you bear?  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: slander the noble name.
    - title: 
      content: "Yes indeed, it is good when you obey the royal law as found in the
        Scriptures: \u201CLove your neighbor as yourself.\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: Lev 19:18.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'But if you favor some people over others, you are committing a sin.
        You are guilty of breaking the law.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the person who keeps all of the laws except one is as guilty
        as a person who has broken all of God\u2019s laws. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the same God who said, \u201CYou must not commit adultery,\u201D
        also said, \u201CYou must not murder.\u201D[COMMENT[0]] So if you murder
        someone but do not commit adultery, you have still broken the law.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: Exod 20:13-14; Deut 5:17-18.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'So whatever you say or whatever you do, remember that you will be
        judged by the law that sets you free. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There will be no mercy for those who have not shown mercy to others.
        But if you have been merciful, God will be merciful when he judges you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Faith without Good Deeds Is Dead
      content: "What good is it, dear brothers and sisters, if you say you have faith
        but don\u2019t show it by your actions? Can that kind of faith save anyone? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Suppose you see a brother or sister who has no food or clothing, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and you say, \u201CGood-bye and have a good day; stay warm and eat
        well\u201D\u2014but then you don\u2019t give that person any food or clothing.
        What good does that do?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So you see, faith by itself isn\u2019t enough. Unless it produces
        good deeds, it is dead and useless.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now someone may argue, \u201CSome people have faith; others have
        good deeds.\u201D But I say, \u201CHow can you show me your faith if you
        don\u2019t have good deeds? I will show you my faith by my good deeds.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You say you have faith, for you believe that there is one God.[COMMENT[0]]
        Good for you! Even the demons believe this, and they tremble in terror. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: 'that God is one; '
        - ft: see Deut 6:4.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "How foolish! Can\u2019t you see that faith without good deeds is
        useless?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t you remember that our ancestor Abraham was shown to be
        right with God by his actions when he offered his son Isaac on the altar? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You see, his faith and his actions worked together. His actions made
        his faith complete. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And so it happened just as the Scriptures say: \u201CAbraham believed
        God, and God counted him as righteous because of his faith.\u201D[COMMENT[0]]
        He was even called the friend of God.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:23a '
        contents:
        - ft: Gen 15:6.
          body: 
      - number: '2:23b '
        contents:
        - ft: See Isa 41:8.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'So you see, we are shown to be right with God by what we do, not
        by faith alone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rahab the prostitute is another example. She was shown to be right
        with God by her actions when she hid those messengers and sent them safely
        away by a different road. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Just as the body is dead without breath,[COMMENT[0]] so also faith
        is dead without good works.
      comments:
      - number: '2:26 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: without spirit.
  - verses:
    - title: Controlling the Tongue
      content: 'Dear brothers and sisters,[COMMENT[0]] not many of you should become
        teachers in the church, for we who teach will be judged more strictly. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'brothers; '
        - ft: also in 3:10.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Indeed, we all make many mistakes. For if we could control our tongues,
        we would be perfect and could also control ourselves in every other way.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We can make a large horse go wherever we want by means of a small
        bit in its mouth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And a small rudder makes a huge ship turn wherever the pilot chooses
        to go, even though the winds are strong. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the same way, the tongue is a small thing that makes grand speeches.\n\tBut
        a tiny spark can set a great forest on fire. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And among all the parts of the body, the tongue is a flame of fire.
        It is a whole world of wickedness, corrupting your entire body. It can set
        your whole life on fire, for it is set on fire by hell itself.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'for it will burn in hell '
        - ft: '(Greek '
          body: Gehenna
        - ft: ).
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'People can tame all kinds of animals, birds, reptiles, and fish, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but no one can tame the tongue. It is restless and evil, full of
        deadly poison. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sometimes it praises our Lord and Father, and sometimes it curses
        those who have been made in the image of God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And so blessing and cursing come pouring out of the same mouth. Surely,
        my brothers and sisters, this is not right! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Does a spring of water bubble out with both fresh water and bitter
        water? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does a fig tree produce olives, or a grapevine produce figs? No,
        and you can\u2019t draw fresh water from a salty spring.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: from salt.
    - title: True Wisdom Comes from God
      content: "If you are wise and understand God\u2019s ways, prove it by living
        an honorable life, doing good works with the humility that comes from wisdom. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you are bitterly jealous and there is selfish ambition in
        your heart, don\u2019t cover up the truth with boasting and lying. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For jealousy and selfishness are not God\u2019s kind of wisdom. Such
        things are earthly, unspiritual, and demonic. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For wherever there is jealousy and selfish ambition, there you will
        find disorder and evil of every kind.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the wisdom from above is first of all pure. It is also peace
        loving, gentle at all times, and willing to yield to others. It is full of
        mercy and the fruit of good deeds. It shows no favoritism and is always sincere. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: And those who are peacemakers will plant seeds of peace and reap a
        harvest of righteousness.[COMMENT[0]]
      comments:
      - number: '3:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'of good things, '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: of justice.
  - verses:
    - title: Drawing Close to God
      content: "What is causing the quarrels and fights among you? Don\u2019t they
        come from the evil desires at war within you? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You want what you don\u2019t have, so you scheme and kill to get
        it. You are jealous of what others have, but you can\u2019t get it, so you
        fight and wage war to take it away from them. Yet you don\u2019t have what
        you want because you don\u2019t ask God for it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And even when you ask, you don\u2019t get it because your motives
        are all wrong\u2014you want only what will give you pleasure.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You adulterers![COMMENT[0]] Don\u2019t you realize that friendship
        with the world makes you an enemy of God? I say it again: If you want to
        be a friend of the world, you make yourself an enemy of God. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: You adulteresses!
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you think the Scriptures have no meaning? They say that God is
        passionate that the spirit he has placed within us should be faithful to
        him.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'They say that the spirit God has placed within us is filled with
            envy; '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: They say that the Holy Spirit, whom God has placed within us, opposes
            our envy.
    - title: 
      content: "And he gives grace generously. As the Scriptures say,\n\t\u201CGod
        opposes the proud\n\tbut gives grace to the humble.\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: Prov 3:34 (Greek version).
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'So humble yourselves before God. Resist the devil, and he will flee
        from you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come close to God, and God will come close to you. Wash your hands,
        you sinners; purify your hearts, for your loyalty is divided between God
        and the world. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let there be tears for what you have done. Let there be sorrow and
        deep grief. Let there be sadness instead of laughter, and gloom instead of
        joy. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Humble yourselves before the Lord, and he will lift you up in honor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Warning against Judging Others
      content: "Don\u2019t speak evil against each other, dear brothers and sisters.[COMMENT[0]]
        If you criticize and judge each other, then you are criticizing and judging
        God\u2019s law. But your job is to obey the law, not to judge whether it
        applies to you. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: brothers.
    - title: 
      content: 'God alone, who gave the law, is the Judge. He alone has the power
        to save or to destroy. So what right do you have to judge your neighbor?  '
      comments: []
    - title: Warning about Self-Confidence
      content: "Look here, you who say, \u201CToday or tomorrow we are going to a
        certain town and will stay there a year. We will do business there and make
        a profit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How do you know what your life will be like tomorrow? Your life is
        like the morning fog\u2014it\u2019s here a little while, then it\u2019s gone. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What you ought to say is, \u201CIf the Lord wants us to, we will
        live and do this or that.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Otherwise you are boasting about your own pretentious plans, and
        all such boasting is evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Remember, it is sin to know what you ought to do and then not do it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Warning to the Rich
      content: 'Look here, you rich people: Weep and groan with anguish because of
        all the terrible troubles ahead of you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your wealth is rotting away, and your fine clothes are moth-eaten
        rags. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your gold and silver are corroded. The very wealth you were counting
        on will eat away your flesh like fire. This corroded treasure you have hoarded
        will testify against you on the day of judgment. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For listen! Hear the cries of the field workers whom you have cheated
        of their pay. The cries of those who harvest your fields have reached the
        ears of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have spent your years on earth in luxury, satisfying your every
        desire. You have fattened yourselves for the day of slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have condemned and killed innocent people,[COMMENT[0]] who do
        not resist you.[COMMENT[1]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:6a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: killed the Righteous One.
      - number: '5:6b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: "Don\u2019t they resist you? "
        - ft: 'or '
          body: "Doesn\u2019t God oppose you? "
        - ft: 'or '
          body: "Aren\u2019t they now accusing you before God?"
    - title: Patience and Endurance
      content: "Dear brothers and sisters,[COMMENT[0]] be patient as you wait for
        the Lord\u2019s return. Consider the farmers who patiently wait for the rains
        in the fall and in the spring. They eagerly look for the valuable harvest
        to ripen. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'brothers; '
        - ft: also in 5:9, 10, 12, 19.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'You, too, must be patient. Take courage, for the coming of the Lord
        is near.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t grumble about each other, brothers and sisters, or you
        will be judged. For look\u2014the Judge is standing at the door!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For examples of patience in suffering, dear brothers and sisters,
        look at the prophets who spoke in the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We give great honor to those who endure under suffering. For instance,
        you know about Job, a man of great endurance. You can see how the Lord was
        kind to him at the end, for the Lord is full of tenderness and mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But most of all, my brothers and sisters, never take an oath, by
        heaven or earth or anything else. Just say a simple yes or no, so that you
        will not sin and be condemned.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Power of Prayer
      content: 'Are any of you suffering hardships? You should pray. Are any of you
        happy? You should sing praises. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Are any of you sick? You should call for the elders of the church
        to come and pray over you, anointing you with oil in the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Such a prayer offered in faith will heal the sick, and the Lord will
        make you well. And if you have committed any sins, you will be forgiven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Confess your sins to each other and pray for each other so that you
        may be healed. The earnest prayer of a righteous person has great power and
        produces wonderful results. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Elijah was as human as we are, and yet when he prayed earnestly that
        no rain would fall, none fell for three and a half years! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then, when he prayed again, the sky sent down rain and the earth
        began to yield its crops.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Restore Wandering Believers
      content: 'My dear brothers and sisters, if someone among you wanders away from
        the truth and is brought back, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: you can be sure that whoever brings the sinner back from wandering
        will save that person from death and bring about the forgiveness of many
        sins.
      comments: []
